HEADWORD: Unform
<hw>Un*form"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>form</ets>.]</ety> <def>To decompose, or resolve
into parts; to destroy the form of; to unmake.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Good.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

